==English==
===Etymology===
From [[German]] ''angst'', from [[Middle High German]] ''[[angest]]'', from [[Old High German]] ''[[angust]]''. See {{pie|angh-}}.

===Pronunciation===
{{ipacregion|Canada}} {{ipac|æŋkst|en-ca-synth-angst.ogg|CA synth}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}
# A feeling of [[acute]] but [[vague]] [[anxiety]] or [[apprehension]] often accompanied by [[depression]], usually reserved for philosophical anxiety.

